<hl>
<seg id=1> Foreign Capital Utilized by China by November Increasing 27% </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, Dec. 17. Although the number of programs to use foreign funds and the amount of contracted foreign funds that China have approved by November this year declined somewhat compared with the same period last year, the actual utilization of foreign capital increased by 27.1% compared with the same period last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The data provided by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation shows that, by November this year, China has in reality utilized foreign funds of $46.959 billion, including direct foreign investments of $40.007 billion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> By November this year, China has ratified 18,644 programs to utilize foreign funds, which declined 15.34% compared with the same period last year. Contracted foreign funds amounted to $48.462 billion, declining by 27.14%. </seg>
<seg id=5> In the newly-approved foreign-funded enterprises, sino-foreign cooperation enterprises and joint ventures, the latter two dropped considerably while the former increased by 4.12%, reaching 8484. </seg>
<seg id=6> The actual foreign invetments incresed by more than 30% compared with the same period last year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> By November this year, China has freshly ratified 13 programs to cooperate with foreign investors, while 10 were ratified in this period last year. </seg>
<seg id=8> Contracted use of foreign funds and actual use of foreign funds are respectively $205 million and $311 million, increasing by 14.53% and 61.98% compared with the same period last year. </seg>
</p>
